modName: Makeovers by Mizzog - College of Winterhold
summary: This mod alters the appearance of the College of Winterhold inhabitants and other related NPCs.
descriptionHtml:
[color=burlywood][font=Comic Sans MS]This is the second mod in a long line of NPC improvements that I started a while back for my game. The first batch were the [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/58101/?]Companions[/url] which was released due to several requests from the flikr community that were Skyrim players. This project is intended as a personal project so please don't freak out if you don't like the way someone looks, there are several other amazing NPC replacers available on the nexus (you can find some links at the bottom of the page). Because there are so many NPCs in this project it would take forever to make each individual character stand alone separate from the group with all their many options and just for the ease of it, an all in one and its many options. I decided to just upload what I create for my game. If I make it, I will share it, but moving forward with the project it will primarily be released Mizz editions. Basic editions might be a possible future update if I feel the need to resort to the same five hair styles over and over.....and over.....and ...over. As I completed the main bulk of my followers, hirelings, and housecarls I started touring my game and noticed that the rest of the Skyrim inhabitants were a little lacking, especially when I ran into Nirya.....YIKES!!. So Since I had Brelyna, J'zargo, and Onmund completed, I felt it was necessary to update the rest of the collage staff which then led to the updates of other related college NPCs.
[size=6][color=olivedrab]---- Mod Includes ----[/color][/size]
[center][color=cornflowerblue][size=5]--- Core College Inhabitants ---[/size][/color][/center]

[center][color=cornflowerblue][size=5]--- NPCs Add-on ---[/size][/color][/center]

[size=4][color=olivedrab]--- Additional Changes made ---[/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[color=cornflowerblue]Brelyna Maryon:
Essential, companion level raised to 81, apprentice destruction robes changed to apprentice alteration with no hood based on primary school of magic.

Jzargo:
Essential, companion level 81, novice robes of conjuration changed to novice robes of destruction with no hood based on primary school of magic.

Onmund:
Essential, companion level 81, novice robes of alteration changed to novice robes of destruction with no hood based on primary school of magic.

Mirabelle Ervine:
Elemental mage and serves as master wizard of the College but wears apprentice robes of alteration and a pair of boots. Changed this to Master Destruction robes to better fit her rank and abilities.

Colette:
Only trains up to expert level spells so I changed her robes from master to expert.

Phinis Gestor:
Only trains up to expert level spells so I changed his robes from master to expert.

Sergius Turrianus:
Changed his adept robes of alteration to expert robes of alteration since he is an expert trainer.

Toldir:
He is already a unique and iconic character. I just made his beard a little thicker.

Falion:
According to Phinis, Falion was his mentor and is a master trainer so I made him a little older than he normally appears.

Psijic Order:
These guys are complete enigmas. I get the order has not been seen in more than a century, but I have no idea how old these elves are. I decided to go with an moderate older look keeping their original white/grey hair as a base for color and even though they are elves, these guys get beards![/color]
[/spoiler]
[size=6][color=olivedrab]---- Recommended Mods ----[/color][/size]
Now just tweaking a jaw shape, narrowing the eye spacing, or even slapping on some new hair wont do the job completely. Your going to need some additional help. Just like my Companions, College of Winterhold is completely at the mercy of what ever skin, hair, and eye texture you the user has installed. I did try something new though! Thanks to Nuska's amazing EEO resources I do have most the elves pointing to EEO face normal maps so if you get some neck seams don't freak, just post a comment with which body normal maps you use and I will do my best to try and make appropriate patches if needed (or if you know what your doing, you can fix it on your on). Also! Thanks to Danriu, I'm using some better looking age maps to try an add a little more detail an uniqueness between characters by using both default path age maps and new path age maps. Below are some recommended mods for the magic endowed characters of Skyrim. Note these are just a few and what I personally use because I love their look. You can use what ever you want, I just provide the face.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36849/?]Immersive College of Winterhold by Grantyboy050[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/35965/?]Dragonborn Mages Robes Retexture Pack by Rafuel[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/34914/?]Psijic Robes Retexture - Keeper of the Ogma HD by Rafuel[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/35089/?]Archmage of Winterhold HD Retexture by Rafuel[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/6129727/?tb=mods&pUp=1]Robes by Lind001[/url] *Great retextures for the non college robes.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/2674/?]Improved NPC Clothing - High Res by BaronDavid[/url] *Used for main college robes
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/58443/?]SkySight Skins - Ultra HD 4K and 2K - Male Textures by fadingsignal[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/32986/?]Mature skin texture and body for UNP(B) 7BASE CBBE Vanilla by Maevan2[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/45453/?]True Daughters of Skyrim by betterbecause[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36510/?]Superior Lore-Friendly Hair - HD textures by skyrimaguas[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/28491/?]Better Vanilla Hairs - Mesh Replacements by kebrus[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/31665/?]Better Makeup for SKSE by Diethardt[/url] *Many options to chose from, I use softer variants.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/30411/?]Brows by Hvergelmir[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/28363/?]Beards by Hvergelmir[/url]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/51343/?]Serenity ENB _ Tranquility ENB by prod80[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/50501/?]The Grim and Somber ENBS by WolfGrimDark[/url]

[size=6][color=olivedrab]---- Installation ----[/color][/size]
[color=red][size=4] !! WARNING !![/size][/color]
[color=chocolate]Installing during the middle of saved game can cause NPCs to loose their gear if their inventory has been altered by the installing mod. Make sure you remove any can't live without gear and dismiss your followers before installing. If you have any naked characters after installation it is ok. Nothing to hit the panic button over and launch a nuclear meltdown. Just open the command screen, press the tilde key...looks like this, `, found next to 1 and above the tab. Click on the naked NPC and type resetinventory and hit enter. Then save your game. Give your follower's gear back and continue gaming.[/color]

[b][color=olivedrab][size=3]Requirements[/size][/color][/b]
Skyrim Update 1.9.32.0
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/19/?]Unofficial Skyrim Patch[/url] by Unofficial Patch Project Team for the USKP users.
To use the high res war paints and tints you MUST have [url=http://skse.silverlock.org/]SKSE[/url] version 1.7.1 or newer installed and you should add these lines to your SKSE.INI:
[color=orange][Display]
iTintTextureResolution=2048[/color]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36849/?]Immersive College of Winterhold[/url] by Grantyboy050 for ICW users

[b][color=olivedrab][size=3]Manual Installation[/size][/color][/b]
1. Download the file to a temporary location such as your desktop or into a folder on your desktop
2. Extract the files using 7zip or winrar
3. Copy and paste all the files into your Skyrim data folder. Usual path is: Steam\SteamApps\common\Skyrim\Data
4. Launch Skyrim, click on "Data Files" and make sure that the plug-in is activated and move it to the bottom of the list.
5. Play the game.

[b][color=olivedrab][size=3]With NMM[/size][/color][/b]
If using Nexus Mod Manager click the “Download with Manager” button and activate the mod to initialize the installer. If you have other mods that alter the appearance of the Companions make sure to load this after unless you have specific single .esps then load them after this mod.

[size=4][color=chocolate]---- Immersive College of Winterhold ----[/color][/size]
When it comes to immersion, Grantyboy050 has done an amazing job to the college. This is the only major college faction changing mod I use and thanks to Grantyboy050 I have his permission to create patches for the NPC improvement options. I've made patches for [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/35002/?]Opulent Outfits[/url] users even though I do not use this mod myself. Just follow the instructions below for ICW and CW by Mizzog.

[b][color=chocolate][size=3]IF USING FOR THE FIRST TIME[/size][/color][/b] Immersive College of Winterhold by Grantyboy050
You must install his mod first. Do not select any of the NPC improvements options, but select all other options if applicable. Install 1 of my main files and the corresponding NPC add-on (if you want the add-on). Last install the corresponding ICW patch from the options section.

[b][color=chocolate][size=3]IF YOU CURENTLY ALREADY HAVE[/size][/color][/b] Immersive College of Winterhold by Grantyboy050 installed, don't fret. You do not need to uninstall and reinstall it, leave it alone. Install 1 of my main files and the corresponding NPC add-on (if you want the add-on). Last install the corresponding ICW patch from the options section. Go to your plugin list and uncheck which ever NPC improvement plugin your are using. Go to your Skyrim data folder and make a backup of your plugin if you wish, but you can delete it at this point.

[b][color=chocolate]Load order should look something like this:[/color][/b]
[color=cornflowerblue]CollegeOfWinterholdImmersive.esp
CWI***Patch [color=orange](Which ever additional patches are required via CWI fomod)[/color]
CW-AIO-by Mizzog [color=orange](Choose 1 of the main files)[/color]
CW by Mizzog - ICW Patch [color=orange](Choose the appropriate main and or NPC add-on related patch)[/color][/color]

[size=6][color=chocolate]---- Uninstalling ----[/color][/size]
[b][color=olivedrab][size=3]Manual Uninstallation[/size][/color][/b]
1. Start Skyrim Launcher, click on Data Files and uncheck "CW by Mizzog.esp" file.
2. Delete all the files from your Skyrim data folder.

[b][color=olivedrab][size=3]Uninstallation Via NMM[/size][/color][/b]
1. Open NMM and double click on "CW by Mizzog" to uninstall.

[size=6][color=red]---- Incompatibilities ----[/color][/size]
While this mod works with any skin and hair textures that you currently use, it is not compatible with any other mod or mods that alter the appearance of any NPCs in this mod. If you wish to use a different version of the same NPC along side this mod, then you must install their mod after mine (or vice versa) and let it overwrite my head meshes and face tints. Otherwise you will need to make patches.
